subSubSection.paragraph:
Cleptes eburnecoxis
sp. n. is closely related to 
Cleptes townesi
Kimsey based on the similar colouration, short MS (0.4 MOD), absence of posterior pit row on pronotum, polished mesopleuron, and posteriorly emarginate T-V. However, it can be distinguished by head being entirely metallic green (the metallic colour is restricted to face in 
Cleptes townesi
), dorsal surface of propodeum with six longitudinal ridges (irregularly reticulate in 
Cleptes townesi
), propodeal angles long and blunt (short and stumpy in 
Cleptes townesi
).

Metasoma. T-I and T-V nearly impunctate; 
T-II-T-IV
with small and dense punctures (Plate 2F). Punctures on T-III denser than those on T-II and T-IV. T-V with the posterior margin emarginate medially.
